# Auth0 Authentication Pattern

This project uses Auth0 Universal Login via the Auth0 SPA SDK (plain HTML/JS).
All auth logic lives in `frontend/Auth0/auth.js`. Never recreate it elsewhere.

## The One Rule

**Do NOT build a custom login form. Do NOT skip Auth0.**

The Explore button must call `LookAuth.login()` which calls `loginWithRedirect()`
and opens the Auth0 hosted login page.

## How to use auth.js on any page

```html
<!-- 1. Include Auth0 SPA SDK -->
<script src="https://cdn.auth0.com/js/auth0-spa-js/2.0/auth0-spa-js.production.js"></script>
<!-- 2. Include the centralised auth module -->
<script src="../Auth0/auth.js"></script>

<script>
  // 3. Init on every page that needs auth
  await LookAuth.init();
  await LookAuth.handleCallback(); // handles ?code=...&state=... on return from Auth0
</script>
```

## Trigger login (e.g. Explore button)

```js
// ✅ CORRECT — opens Auth0 Universal Login
LookAuth.login(); // calls loginWithRedirect() internally

// ❌ WRONG — never do this
window.location.href = 'login.html';
```

## Post-auth routing (already handled in auth.js)

```
Auth0 redirects back → handleCallback() → check localStorage profile
  No profile  → onboarding.html   (new user)
  Has profile → dashboard.html    (existing user)
```

## Auth0 Dashboard checklist (REQUIRED or Auth0 never opens)

Add to Allowed Callback URLs, Logout URLs, and Web Origins:
- `http://localhost:8080`   (python3 -m http.server 8080)
- `http://localhost:5173`   (if using Vite)
- your deployed URL when live

## Credentials location

`frontend/Auth0/auth.js` — fill in `AUTH0_DOMAIN` and `AUTH0_CLIENT_ID`.
Never hardcode credentials anywhere else.
